title: List of Macarthur FC seasons
text:
<a href="Macarthur%20FC">Macarthur Football Club</a> is an Australian professional <a href="association%20football">association football</a> club based in <a href="Macarthur%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Macarthur</a>, <a href="Sydney">Sydney</a>. The club was formed in 2017 as Macarthur South West United before it was shortly renamed to Macarthur FC in 2019. They were admitted into the <a href="A-League%20Men">A-League Men</a> in 2020, having spent the 2018–19 season playing their one friendly game.
History.
When the Macarthur FC bid for the <a href="A-League%20Men">A-League Men</a> was founded in 2017 as Macarthur South West United, they played their first match against <a href="Central%20Coast%20Mariners%20FC">Central Coast Mariners</a> in October 2018. Two months later, they successfully won the bid for the <a href="Expansion%20of%20the%20A-League%20Men">expansion</a> for <a href="2019%E2%80%9320%20A-League">2019–20 A-League</a> season. Their inaugural season had the team finish 6th to finish in the semi-finals.
